  "prompt": "How do I know if a shy guy likes me?",
  "response": "It can be tricky to tell if a shy guy likes you because they often don't express their feelings overtly. However, there are subtle signs you can look for. Here's a breakdown of things to watch out for:\n\n**Body Language Cues:**\n\n*   **Eye Contact (and Aversion):** This is a big one.\n    *   **Frequent glances:** He might sneak peeks at you when he thinks you're not looking. If you catch him, he might quickly look away.\n    *   **Prolonged eye contact (rare but potent):** If he manages to hold your gaze for a few seconds longer than normal, it could be a sign.\n    *   **Avoiding eye contact altogether:** Ironically, extreme shyness can make a guy avoid eye contact entirely. It doesn't necessarily mean he *doesn't* like you, just that he's nervous.\n*   **Mirroring:** Subconsciously mimicking your body language (posture, gestures, etc.) can be a sign of attraction.\n*   **Nervous Fidgeting:** Fidgeting, playing with his hair, shifting his weight, or generally appearing restless when you're around can indicate nervousness, which might stem from liking you.\n*   **Proximity:** Does he often find excuses to be near you? Does he position himself close to you in a group setting?\n*   **Posture:** Does he stand up straighter or try to present himself better when you're around?\n*   **Blushing:** Blushing easily or frequently when talking to you is a classic sign of nervousness and potential attraction.\n*   **Smiles:** Even small, fleeting smiles can be significant, especially if they're genuine and accompanied by a shy glance.\n\n**Verbal and Interaction Clues:**\n\n*   **Talking More (or Less) Around You:**\n    *   **Increased talking:** He might try to engage you in conversation more often than he does with others, even if the conversations are brief or about mundane things.\n    *   **Quiet around you:** He might become quieter or withdrawn when you're nearby. This could be due to being nervous and not knowing what to say.\n*   **Initiating Conversations (Even Small Ones):** Does he go out of his way to say \"hi\" or ask you about your day, even if it's just a quick exchange?\n*   **Remembering Details:** Does he remember things you've told him in the past, even seemingly insignificant details? This shows he's paying attention and cares about what you say.\n*   **Inside Jokes/Shared Moments:** Does he refer back to inside jokes or shared experiences? This shows he values those connections with you.\n*   **Teasing (Playful, not Mean):** Light, playful teasing (not bullying or being mean) can be a way for him to test the waters and gauge your reaction.\n*   **Active Listening:** Does he make an effort to listen attentively when you're talking? Does he ask follow-up questions?\n*   **Offering Help:** Does he offer to help you with things, even small tasks? This could be a way for him to show he cares and wants to be helpful.\n*   **Online/Texting Behavior:** If you communicate online, look for:\n    *   **Quick responses (or anxious delays):** He might respond to your messages quickly because he's eager to talk to you. Conversely, he might take a long time to respond because he's overthinking his replies.\n    *   **Asking questions:** Does he ask you questions about yourself, your interests, or your day?\n    *   **Using emojis:** Does he use emojis to add warmth and expressiveness to his messages?\n*   **Compliments (Subtle or Genuine):** Shy guys often avoid direct compliments, but they might offer subtle ones. Look for compliments on your work, your ideas, or your sense of humor. A rare direct compliment could be very meaningful.\n\n**Social Clues:**\n\n*   **Changes in Behavior:** Has his behavior changed noticeably since you've become closer?\n*   **Friends' Reactions:** Are his friends acting differently around you? Are they teasing him, smiling knowingly, or making subtle hints? They might know something you don't.\n*   **Jealousy (Subtle):** Does he seem a bit put out or uncomfortable when you talk about other guys? This can be a subtle sign of jealousy.\n*   **Paying Attention to Your Interests:** Does he start showing an interest in things you like, even if they weren't things he was into before?\n\n**How to Test the Waters (Without Being Overly Direct):**\n\n*   **Increase your own level of interaction:** Initiate conversations, smile at him, and make eye contact. See how he responds.\n*   **Give him opportunities to talk:** Ask him open-ended questions that require more than just a \"yes\" or \"no\" answer.\n*   **Be approachable and friendly:** Make it clear that you're open to talking to him.\n*   **Suggest a casual activity:** Suggest doing something together that isn't overtly romantic, like grabbing coffee or working on a project together. This gives him a chance to spend time with you in a low-pressure setting.\n*   **Pay attention to his reactions to your efforts:** Does he reciprocate your efforts? Does he seem to enjoy spending time with you?\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Every shy guy is different:** Not all shy guys will exhibit all of these signs. Some may be more subtle than others.\n*   **Don't overanalyze:** Try not to get too caught up in analyzing every single interaction.\n*   **Be patient:** It might take time to figure out how he feels.\n*   **Focus on getting to know him:** The best way to know for sure is to get to know him as a person and see if you have a genuine connection.\n*   **Respect his shyness:** Don't pressure him to open up before he's ready.\n*   **Be prepared for either outcome:** He may or may not like you romantically. Be prepared to accept either outcome gracefully.\n\n**Ultimately, the best way to know for sure is to be brave and ask him how he feels, but understand that approach may be too forward for some shy individuals. Start slowly, build a connection, and watch for the signs. Good luck!**\n",
